text: Dude I’m so down for this. I was never interested in the other fast and furious films, and this has me on board just from how it’s going in a different direction. This looks fun and crazy with two really awesome leads. I just want this to be wacky af with awesomely delivered wacky one liners. Idris Elba looks like he knows what movie he’s in and seems to know his place as the wacky villain, unlike Charlize Theron’s character which was just such a drag and unnecessarily dark for the type of movie she was in. This is a spin off people, it’s not a Fast and Furious film. And besides, they’re doing something with different, leaning in on the craziness and taking advantage of their lead actors’ charisma rather than milking the same dead Vin-Diesel-taking-the-movie-he’s-in-too-seriously cow.

The whole series has been nothing like the originals with cars and racing with the emphasis on cops vs criminals thing I remember and they continually put like a massive “impossible scenario” spin on every entry and inject cars where it really doesn’t need it, the last one was fucking no where near the first one where it goes from cops to basically Avengers doomsday. It was basically James Bond: infinity wars, like I get it you have this universe and what not, but it’s not really a fast and furious movie anymore, there is no racing or cop vs thug need 4 speed vibe, sure there is cars but it’s basically watching death race or twisted metal at this point. So take it into its natural progress a super badass, dumb ass puns, child style humor and physic defying mayhem Already. And they finally took the leap and I’m happy, hopefully none of those other guys like Dom and that dumbass black guy show up though, Dwayne Johnson and Jason Stathem, is all we need and ofc Idris Elba is an amazing actor. I’ve have never been more willing to see a fast and a furious before, but still it begs the question why is fast and furious even in the title, they could sell this alone with the actors ALONE.

The only thing that stood out were characters like Hobbs and Shaw who seem to have an interesting chemistry on screen. So to walk away from what was being passed off as “the fast and furious” sequels, this actually might be a breathe of fresh air.
